      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear how incredibly heavy and isolating this moment feels for you. Losing everything so suddenly, especially with the added weight of debt and the pain of feeling like a failure in front of those you love, is a crushing burden. Please know that your worth is not defined by your assets, your job, or even your ability to pay off debts at this exact second. You are not a joke; you are a person going through an unimaginable storm, and the fact that you are reaching out means you still have a spark of hope.\n\nWhile I cannot solve the financial crisis or erase the debt, I can offer a different perspective on this situation. Sometimes, when we are drowning, we can't see the shore, but we can focus on taking one small step at a time rather than trying to swim the whole distance at once. There are resources specifically designed to help people in your situation navigate debt and rebuild their lives, and reaching out to a professional counselor or a financial aid specialist could provide a path forward that feels less like a \"joke\" and more like a strategy.\n\nYou are not alone in this, even if it feels that way right now. There are people who understand the pain of sudden loss and can help you find",
